videos.headline: Sam Curran to Maharaj, out Caught by Livingstone!! Holes out! 125.4kph, full and in the slot, Maharaj clears his front leg to go over long-on. The bat turns and hence the timing goes awry. Hits it straight to Livingstone who doesn't err on this occasion. Excellent comeback from Curran after conceding a couple of boundaries in this over. Maharaj c Livingstone b Sam Curran 1(2)

Sam Curran to Powell, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! Edged and gone! Powell is walking. Banged in short outside off, Powell probably didn't expect it. Good lift outside off and Powell looks to pull through backward square leg. Not a convincing shot and all he manages to get is a faint top edge. Jitesh Sharma doesn't err. Punjab continue to fight. Powell c Jitesh Sharma b Sam Curran 11(5) [4s-2]

Harshal Patel to Dhruv Jurel, out Caught by Shashank Singh!! Shashank Singh takes a good catch! 133.9kph, Dhruv Jurel walks across to heave this short of a good length ball over the leg-side. Hits him high on the bat and Shashank runs in from deep midwicket and slides to gobble it up. Dhruv Jurel c Shashank Singh b Harshal Patel 6(11)

Arshdeep Singh to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Rabada!! The slower ball does the trick! 120.5kph, pace off and into the wicket, Riyan Parag spots the length but is a bit early into his pull shot. Top-edges, more height than distance. Rabada, at deep midwicket, calls for it, settles under it and takes a calm catch. The in-form Parag departs for 23, wasn't at his fluent best today. Riyan Parag c Rabada b Arshdeep Singh 23(18) [4s-1 6s-1]

Rabada to Samson, out Lbw!! 134.3kph, vociferous appeal for lbw and up goes Anil Kumar Chaudhary's finger. Samson reluctantly reviews. Lack of bounce from a back of a length, Samson shapes to pull and misses as the ball scoots under his blade. Struck on the back thigh adjacent to the sticks and that's hitting middle! RR lose their captain as well as a review. Big wicket for Punjab who continue to fight. Replays show that it was a leg-cutter from Rabada which wasn't picked by the batter. Samson lbw b Rabada 18(14) [4s-1 6s-1]

Rabada to Samson, out Lbw!! 134.3kph, vociferous appeal for lbw and up goes Anil Kumar Chaudhary's finger. Samson reluctantly reviews. Lack of bounce from a back of a length, Samson shapes to pull and misses as the ball scoots under his blade. Struck on the back thigh adjacent to the sticks and that's hitting middle! RR lose their captain as well as a review. Big wicket for Punjab who continue to fight. Replays show that it was a leg-cutter from Rabada which wasn't picked by the batter. Samson lbw b Rabada 18(14) [4s-1 6s-1]

Rabada to Jaiswal, out Caught by Harshal Patel!! Rabada comes back to remove Jaiswal. Banged in short outside off, Jaiswal clears his front leg and goes after it. Flashes his bat hard for an upper-cut but gets it off the bottom part of the bat. Ends up hitting it straight down third man's throat. Jaiswal falls after getting a start. Jaiswal c Harshal Patel b Rabada 39(28) [4s-4]

Livingstone to Tanush Kotian, out Bowled!! Gone! This was on the cards. Plenty of dot balls, he tries to slog his way out of trouble and perishes in the process. Pushed quicker and flatter by Livingstone, Kotian shimmies down the track to swing it over midwicket. Got saved by an inside edge last ball but this time he misses it altogether to hear the death rattle. Tanush Kotian b Livingstone 24(31) [4s-3]

Boult to Ashutosh Sharma, out Caught by Maharaj!! Ashutosh Sharma falls after playing a gem of a cameo! A short ball that rushes Ashutosh Sharma for pace. He looks to pull it across but top-edges it towards backward point. Maharaj makes no mistake. Ashutosh Sharma c Maharaj b Boult 31(16) [4s-1 6s-3]

Chahal to Ashutosh Sharma, out Livingstone Run Out!! 1 run completed! Tossed up full ball on middle and leg, Ashutosh Sharma drags his heave towards deep mid-wicket. Livingstone wants the second but he has been sent back. He is struggling to get back as Samson collects the flat throw to his left and gets low to throw it back onto the stumps. It is taken upstairs and Livingstone is short. Brilliant tag-team work from Kotian and Samson. Livingstone run out (Tanush Kotian/Samson) 21(14) [4s-2 6s-1]

Avesh Khan to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by Riyan Parag!! Avesh gets his second wicket! A skiddy good length ball angling in on off, Jitesh Sharma tries to go over mid-off but he completely miscues it. Parag inside the ring takes an easy catch. Jitesh Sharma looked promising tonight but fell before his innings could blossom. Jitesh Sharma c Riyan Parag b Avesh Khan 29(24) [4s-1 6s-2]

Kuldeep Sen to Shashank Singh, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! They're finding the fielders everywhere tonight - back of a length and angling into the right-hander, Shashank picked the length and then swivelled across on the pull, he got a lot of height and no real distance, high and down Jurel's throat, who completes his 3rd catch of the night, running to his left from deep square leg. Shashank Singh c Dhruv Jurel b Kuldeep Sen 9(9) [4s-1]

Maharaj to Sam Curran, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel at deep mid-wicket!! Catching practice at deep mid-wicket, nothing is going right for the Punjab KIngs at the moment. Dropped short by Maharaj and the pull was on - Curran rocked back on the shot, but he's hit it off the lower half of the bat, dragged the pull towards deep mid-wicket where Jurel ran in, slid forward and took a fine catch. Sam Curran c Dhruv Jurel b Maharaj 6(10)

Maharaj to Bairstow, out Caught by Hetmyer!! That's the end of a laborious knock and it's also Maharaj's first IPL wicket. He tossed up one slower and just outside off, a hint of spin and Bairstow had to reach out on the drive after having backed away initially, hit high on the bat and spooned for a dolly to Hetmyer at cover. He never got going tonight and has had a painful stay ended. Bairstow c Hetmyer b Maharaj 15(19) [4s-1]

Chahal to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! That's ugly and Prabhsimran has holed out to wide long-on - came down the pitch, got too close to the ball, no timing on the lofted drive, hits it into the wind and the ball sails down the throat of Jurel, who doesn't drop those. A first-over wicket for Chahal and Punjab continue to struggle. Prabhsimran c Dhruv Jurel b Chahal 10(14) [4s-1]

Avesh Khan to Atharva Taide, out Caught by Kuldeep Sen!! A massive top-edge on the pull, goes straight up and Samson calls for the catch, so does Kuldeep at short third man, a minor collision, but Kuldeep held on and has a word with his captain, was always his catch and he makes Samson know. Banged in short and following Taide as he came down the pitch, he tries to pull, gets cramped for room and only manages a top-edge - Kuldeep didn't have to move an inch as he accepted it with glee. Atharva Taide c Kuldeep Sen b Avesh Khan 15(12) [4s-2]
